---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Base64 Encoder & Decoder"
  description="Encode text to Base64 or decode Base64 to text instantly. Free online Base64 tool for developers. No data sent to servers."
>
  <div id="b64-app">
    <div>
      <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Input</label>
      <textarea
        id="b64-input"
        rows="6"
        placeholder="Enter text to encode, or Base64 string to decode..."
        class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm font-mono resize-y focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:border-transparent"
      ></textarea>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-4">
      <button id="b64-encode" class="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-colors">
        Encode to Base64
      </button>
      <button id="b64-decode" class="bg-gray-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">
        Decode from Base64
      </button>
      <button id="b64-swap" class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors">
        Swap Input/Output
      </button>
      <button id="b64-copy" class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors">
        Copy Output
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="b64-status" class="mt-3 text-sm hidden"></div>

    <div class="mt-4">
      <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-2">Output</label>
      <textarea
        id="b64-output"
        rows="6"
        readonly
        class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm font-mono bg-gray-50 resize-y"
      ></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 prose prose-sm max-w-none">
    <h2>Free Online Base64 Encoder and Decoder</h2>
    <p>Encode text to Base64 format or decode Base64 strings back to plain text. Base64 encoding is commonly used for transmitting binary data over text-based protocols like email and HTTP. Essential tool for web developers.</p>
    <h3>What is Base64?</h3>
    <p>Base64 is a binary-to-text encoding scheme that represents binary data in an ASCII string format. It is commonly used in data URLs, email attachments (MIME), JSON Web Tokens (JWT), and API authentication headers.</p>
    <h3>Common Use Cases</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Embedding images as data URLs in HTML/CSS</li>
      <li>Encoding API credentials for HTTP Basic Authentication</li>
      <li>Decoding JWT token payloads</li>
      <li>Transmitting binary data in JSON</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use the Base64 Encoder & Decoder</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3 text-gray-600">
      <li><strong>Enter your input</strong> — Paste plain text to encode, or a Base64 string to decode, into the input box.</li>
      <li><strong>Choose an action</strong> — Click "Encode to Base64" to convert text to Base64, or "Decode from Base64" to convert a Base64 string back to readable text.</li>
      <li><strong>View the output</strong> — The result appears instantly in the output box with a status message showing the character count before and after conversion.</li>
      <li><strong>Swap or copy</strong> — Use "Swap Input/Output" to quickly re-encode or re-decode, or "Copy Output" to copy the result to your clipboard.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">What is Base64 encoding and why is it used?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Base64 is a method of encoding binary data into ASCII text characters. It is used when binary data needs to be transmitted over text-based systems like email (MIME), URLs, or JSON APIs. The encoded output is about 33% larger than the original data.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">How do I decode a Base64 string?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Paste the Base64 string into the input box and click "Decode from Base64". The decoded plain text will appear in the output box. If the input is not valid Base64, the tool will show an error message explaining the issue.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is Base64 encoding the same as encryption?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">No, Base64 is not encryption and should never be used for security purposes. It is simply an encoding format that can be easily reversed by anyone. If you need to protect sensitive data, use proper encryption methods like AES or RSA instead.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Does this tool support UTF-8 and special characters?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes, this tool fully supports UTF-8 encoding. You can encode and decode text containing emojis, accented characters, Chinese characters, and other Unicode content. The tool uses the TextEncoder/TextDecoder API to handle all character sets correctly.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is my data safe when using this Base64 tool?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes, all encoding and decoding happens entirely in your browser using JavaScript. No data is sent to any server. This makes the tool safe for encoding API keys, tokens, and other sensitive strings that you would not want transmitted over the internet.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<script>
  const inputEl = document.getElementById('b64-input') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const outputEl = document.getElementById('b64-output') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const statusEl = document.getElementById('b64-status')!;

  function showStatus(msg: string, isError: boolean) {
    statusEl.textContent = msg;
    statusEl.className = `mt-3 text-sm p-3 rounded-lg ${isError ? 'bg-red-50 text-red-700 border border-red-200' : 'bg-green-50 text-green-700 border border-green-200'}`;
    statusEl.classList.remove('hidden');
  }

  document.getElementById('b64-encode')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    try {
      const encoder = new TextEncoder();
      const data = encoder.encode(inputEl.value);
      let binary = '';
      data.forEach(b => binary += String.fromCharCode(b));
      outputEl.value = btoa(binary);
      showStatus(`Encoded! ${inputEl.value.length} chars → ${outputEl.value.length} Base64 chars`, false);
    } catch (e: any) {
      showStatus(`Error: ${e.message}`, true);
    }
  });

  document.getElementById('b64-decode')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    try {
      const binary = atob(inputEl.value.trim());
      const bytes = new Uint8Array(binary.length);
      for (let i = 0; i < binary.length; i++) bytes[i] = binary.charCodeAt(i);
      outputEl.value = new TextDecoder().decode(bytes);
      showStatus(`Decoded! ${inputEl.value.length} Base64 chars → ${outputEl.value.length} chars`, false);
    } catch (e: any) {
      showStatus(`Invalid Base64: ${e.message}`, true);
    }
  });

  document.getElementById('b64-swap')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const temp = inputEl.value;
    inputEl.value = outputEl.value;
    outputEl.value = temp;
  });

  document.getElementById('b64-copy')!.addEventListener('click', () => {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(outputEl.value);
  });
</script>
